main event: On April 9, 1964, a bright oblong object was observed in Oak Lawn, Illinois, for 20 seconds.
interesting points: The object was described as bright and oblong with slow movement and no sound,The sighting lasted for about 20 seconds,The object did not leave a trail in its flight,No identification could be determined for the object based on the available data,There are indications that the slow flight may not correspond to any conventional aircraft.
